parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal Failure due to Dry-Rotting Rubber Mounts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signals can lead to accidents, especially when the signals are hanging by the wires, causing a distraction to the driver and other road users. Additionally, the melting of the plastic on the muffler can cause further damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Turn signals fall off
rubber mounts dry-rot and break
signals hang by wires
signals melt onto the muffler
and the vehicle's electrical system is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter idler gear shaft can cause the engine to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, or engine damage.
symptoms: Grinding noise when trying to crank the bike
starter gear shaft migration out of the left side engine cover
unsupportive gear on the inboard side
and potential transmission lock-up or timing chain skipping teeth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine seizure, failure, or costly damage, potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal oil consumption
oil leaks
engine consuming 8-10 ounces of oil per thousand miles
and potential engine seizure or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the muffler mounting bolts can cause the muffler to separate from the vehicle, leading to accidents or serious injury.
symptoms: Muffler fell off while riding
all three mounting bolts fell out
and potential crash or serious injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear shock pre-load adjuster can lead to improper suspension settings, which can cause hazardous riding conditions, especially when carrying a passenger or heavy loads.
symptoms: The pre-load adjuster spins freely
the pre-load adjuster breaks
the shock remains on the softest setting
unable to be adjusted
the pre-load adjuster fails to adjust the pre-load
the shock absorber pre-load adjuster is broken.
